<TEXT>
some facts and figures on the assemblies of god church 
founded in 1914 during a convention in hot springs ark the 
assemblies of god moved its headquarters to springfield mo from 
st louis in 1918 it employs more than 1300 people in 
springfield at the headquarters its seminary three colleges and 
a retirement center 
the assemblies of god is pentecostal a branch of christianity 
emphasizing personal experience of god manifested in gifts of 
the spirit such as speaking in tongues and healing 
it is the largest pentecostal demonination if the united 
states claiming nearly 25 million adherents plus 14 million 
overseas 9 million of them in brazil 
there are nearly 11000 assemblies of god churches in the 
united states and more than 30000 ministers about 3700 of them 
women according to a 1987 survey 
the church is composed of 57 districts primarily broken down 
by geographic boundaries 
ordained ministers and church delegates form the general 
council a body which meets biennially to conduct church business 
formulate procedures and policies and elect top executive officers 
to the 13member executive presbytery the general superintendent 
who is the top executive officer is elected to a fouryear term 
all others are elected to twoyear terms 
ministers can be disciplined not only for moral indescretion 
but also for straying from church doctrines inefficency being 
contentious or noncooperative or trying to assume dictatorial 
power over a congregation 
</TEXT>
