<TEXT>
a 15year search for meteorites in 
antarctica has turned up thousands of meteorites including six 
from the moon and one possible rock from mars scientists say 
those seven meteorites solid bodies that travel through space 
and survive passage through the earths atmosphere have been the 
focus of years of scrutiny by scientists looking for insight on the 
composition of the two heavenly bodies 
it has always been assumed that a lot of material should be 
falling off the moon from meteoritic impact said ursula b 
marvin a geologist at the smithsonian institutions center for 
astrophysics here we suspected that some of our meteorites came 
from the moon before the apollo missions 
marvin was part of the us expedition that discovered the 
plumsized rock weighing about four grams in january 1982 
japanese scientists have located five lunar meteorites in 
antarctica scientists also are building a case for martian 
origin of the meteorite found in 1979 
comparing the 1982 find with lunar samples collected by american 
astronauts scientists found the meteorite closely matched highland 
materials returned by the apollo 15 16 and 17 crews 
analysis indicated that the fragment was blasted away from the 
moon by an asteroid impact about 100000 years ago and hurled to 
earth 
the 66yearold marvin who also teaches parttime at harvard 
university said the lunar meteorite probably was traveling in 
space for between 1900 and 2500 years before crashing through the 
atmosphere and landing on the antarctic ice 
the antarctic rock believed to be from mars spent about 10 
million years in space 
some of the 1000 moon rocks retrieved in the apollo missions 
have been dated at more than 4 billion years old a short time by 
geologic standards 
xrays and gammarays of the moons surface taken by apollo 
orbiters have led scientists to believe the lunar meteorite may 
come from a crater on the fareastern rim of the moon or on the 
unexplored dark side marvin said 
we went to six places on the moon and the russians sent 
unmanned landers to three places she said we have no exact 
location for this composition anywhere 
annual us meteorite expeditions to antarctica occur in the six 
weeks of the year when the continent is bathed in sunlight 24 hours 
a day 
the national science foundation the national aeronautics and 
space administration and the smithsonian provide equipment and 
financing for research for the meteoritic expeditions said marvin 
who has has made three trips to the 5millionsquaremile continent 
to search for meteorites 
she said that since manned moon exploration stopped after the 
apollo 17 mission in 1972 meteorite searches are crucial 
its one of the most vital and productive aspects of the space 
program marvin said as a matter of fact in planetary 
exploration its the only show in town this all gives us more 
information without actually going up there about the evolution 
of the moon as a body 
