<TEXT>
the supreme court today agreed to judge the 
validity of a 5 percent tax illinois imposes on all telephone calls 
charged to instate numbers 
the court said it will study arguments that the tax interferes 
impermissibly with interstate commerce 
the tax is assessed at a flat rate on all calls intrastate and 
interstate charged to illinois service addresses 
two state residents jerome f goldberg and robert mctigue 
challenged the law in a classaction lawsuit three years ago in 
chicago gte sprint communications corp joined the case later 
seeking to recover taxes already paid 
from sept 15 1985 to july 1986 gte sprint paid 26 million 
in taxes under the challenged illinois telecommunications excise 
tax 
the illinois supreme court upheld the tax last june 24 
reversing a state appeals court ruling that had invalidated it 
the appeals court had said illinois is attempting to tax the 
entire cost of an interstate act which takes place only partially 
in illinois 
the appeals court had added this tax discriminates 
against interstate commerce and it is not related to services 
provided in illinois 
the state supreme court acknowledged that illinois is taxing the 
gross charge of an entire interstate call even though the 
benefits it affords are limited to that portion of the 
communication occurring within the state 
but it said the tax does not unduly burden interstate commerce 
the two state residents and gte sprint filed separate supreme 
court appeals and the national taxpayers union urged the justices 
as a friend of the court to strike down the tax 
its brief argued 
if illinois attempted to tax united parcel service on the 
entire value of its service for all packages picked up in the 
state regardless of where they were delivered that tax would fall 
before the constitutions commerce clause telecommunications 
companies whether they are in the telephone telegraph or 
electronic data transmission business provide a service which for 
many purposes is functionally identical 
the cases are goldberg vs sweet 87826 and gte sprint vs 
sweet 871101 
</TEXT>
