the supreme court said monday it will judge 
the validity of a federal law that lets independent counsels 
investigate alleged crimes by highranking executive branch 
officials 
the court also rejected the latest appeal of one target of such 
an investigation marine lt col oliver l north 
the courts decision expected by july will resolve a major 
constitutional dispute and will affect the criminal conviction of 
former white house aide michael k deaver and the rejuvenated 
investigation of exjustice department official theodore b olson 
the decision also could affect other investigations by special 
prosecutors appointed under the law 
the justices allowed special prosecutor alexia morrison to 
resume her investigation of olson raising the possibility that 
grand jury indictments could be handed down before the high courts 
ruling 
a federal appeals court ruled that the watergateera law 
creating independent counsels impermissibly gives presidential 
appointment powers to the federal courts the appeals court had 
derailed morrisons investigation 
a threejudge panel of the us circuit court of appeals in 
washington ruled by a 21 vote last month that the independent 
counsel provisions of the ethics in government act of 1978 were an 
unconstitutional encroachment of the exclusive power of the 
president to enforce criminal laws 
under the law a special court appoints independent counsels or 
special prosecutors at the request of the attorney general to 
investigate alleged criminal wrongdoing 
morrison is investigating allegations that olson a former 
assistant attorney general lied to congress in 1983 during a 
dispute over the environmental protection agencys cleanup program 
for toxic waste 
the appeals court ruling followed a challenge by olson and 
others to morrisons authority to subpoena their testimony before a 
federal grand jury 
the jan 22 ruling could jeopardize last months perjury 
conviction of former presidential aide michael k deaver for lying 
to a grand jury and to a house subcommittee that investigated his 
lobbying activities 
but the appeals court ruling in olsons case is not expected to 
interfere with the work of lawrence e walsh the independent 
counsel investigating the irancontra arms and money affair 
the supreme court last month refused to consider norths 
challenge to the parallel appointment walsh accepted last year from 
the justice department 
north was fired as a white house aide after his role in the 
diversion of money from secret iranian arms sales to the nicaraguan 
contra rebels was revealed 
a different threejudge panel of the appeals court in washington 
upheld the constitutionality of the backup appointments last year 
independent counsel james c mckay who is prosecuting former 
presidential aide lyn c nofziger on illegal lobbying charges also 
accepted a backup appointment 
but morrison and whitney north seymour the independent counsel 
who prosecuted deaver did not accept backup appointments 
the north appeal acted on monday was from a ruling that barred 
him from halting walshs investigation by challenging its legality 
in a civil lawsuit 
the appeals court ruling that dismissed norths lawsuit said 
potential criminal defendants cannot by bringing ancillary 
equitable proceedings circumvent federal criminal procedure 
