<TEXT>
a contingency plan to help prevent an 
uncontrolled meltdown of the financial markets won the endorsement 
monday of the chairman of the house energy and commerce committee 
and three other representatives 
our markets remain vibrant but they are at the same time 
delicate rep john dingell dmich wrote in a letter to the 
heads of three regulatory agencies to permit them to function 
without such a contingency plan courts unnecessary risk 
the letter was also signed by reps edward markey dmass 
chairman of the house telecommunications and finance subcommittee 
norman lent rny ranking minority member on the energy and 
commerce committee and matthew rinaldo rnj ranking minority 
member of the finance subcommittee 
the letter to the securities and exchange commission commodity 
futures trading commission and federal reserve board was prompted 
by the oct 19 stock crash 
the market decline was a wrenching and sobering experience 
for the marketplace market participants regulators and those of 
us in congress with oversight responsibilities for our securities 
markets the letter said 
it noted a recommendation by the general accounting office 
congress research arm that regulators prepare a plan for dealing 
with any similar emergency in the future 
we believe that his recommendation should be implemented 
as a concrete first step toward increased coordination among the 
markets and restoration of investor confidence the letter said 
the congressmen asked the regulators to report to congress by 
march 25 on their efforts to craft a plan for coordinating 
decisions by regulators and communicating them to the markets 
they also asked the agencies to determine how much authority 
the marketplaces should have to act independently of the regulators 
in crisis circumstances 
the letter urged the agencies to agree on circumstances that 
would allow relaxed interpretation of rules to facilitate market 
liquidity such as the interpretation of rules associated with 
corporate stock repurchase plans and on the provision of funds 
to the economy by the federal reserve during times of market 
turmoil 
congress meanwhile has been considering longterm measures to 
ensure greater market coordination ranging from a partial merger 
of the sec and cftc to the creation of a new oversight body 
