chairman of the skazka cooperative took home 1050 more than 
three times the average soviet wage of 330 
the building that now contains the restaurant was once a bar 
favored by lyubers bodybuilding enthusiasts from a moscow 
suburb that some press reports have said prey on longhaired soviet 
youths who like western rock music 
either because of its tough clientele or because the 
healthconscious lyubers did not drink enough alcohol the bar lost 
money kutuzov said 
