<TEXT>
fourteen candidates of various 
political hues are in the race for venezuelas presidency but 
polls give two centrists the leading edge so far in the campaign 
for decembers balloting 
a former antigovernment guerrilla hopes to become a serious 
third option but the other 11 candidates are given little chance 
one of the centrists is eduardo fernandez who is known as the 
tiger the other is carlos andres perez a former president who 
has been matching practically every every campaign promise 
fernandez has made 
the former guerrilla is teodoro petkoff a socialist 
fernandez and perez represent the two political parties that 
have dominated venezuelan politics since dictator marcos perez 
jimenez was overthrown in 1958 after six years in power 
accion democratica ad the social democratic party now in 
power is fielding perez a 69yearold charismatic leader with 
considerable political experience 
perezs government in 197377 is popularly associated with the 
oilprices boom in 1974 
he is considered to have a slight edge now for the dec 4 
election although the 47yearold fernandez the copei or 
christian democratic party candidate has made inroads by raising 
the issue of electoral reform 
