copei a member of the christian democratic organization of 
america is considered somewhat more conservative while ad which 
belongs to the socialist international is more labororiented 
but they are both centrist their members run from conservative 
to liberal but most are somewhere in between 
venezuelas presidency has flipped back and forth between the ad 
and copei five times in the six elections from 1958 to 1983 an ad 
candidate succeeded an ad president only once 
their success in dominating venezuelan politics has relegated 
all the other parties to marginal political roles 
the exguerrilla petkoff is carrying the banner of the 
movimiento al socialismo 
in the 1960s when an indigenous guerrilla movement was active 
petkoff preached a socialism bordering on communism 
but he gave up his fight accepting amnesty offered by the 
government he moderated his views and is now a member of congress 
his party dropped its affiliation with moscow following the 
sovietled invasion of czechoslavakia in 1968 
but even though petkoff started his campaign by trimming his 
bushy moustache and longish hair in an effort to dispel any 
conceptions of radicalism he isnt expected to win much more than 
5 percent of the vote 
that was as much as his party got into 1978 its best year 
the remaining candidates are even worse off they are formally 
in the race but are not making much of a difference 
venezuelas first woman presidential candidate ismenia 
villalba is running on the slogan ismenia take her into your 
heart 
