<TEXT>
concert pianist eugene istomin has loaded his 
steinway on a van and is driving from town to town for his 1988 
tour an unusual way for classical musicians to hit the road 
it hasnt been done this way for 50 years at least istomin 
says paderewski the polish pianist and composer who died in 
1941 had a private railroad car 
there are a lot of places on my tour where socalled big 
name artists dont go the seating capacity of halls is small and 
people cant afford to pay very high fees istomin is accepting 
what he terms reasonable fees 
im playing in a lot of communities which would otherwise not 
hear me on a magnificently prepared superb piano playing a good 
program its giving me a lot of gratification 
from january through may his solo piano recitals are east of 
chicago the western tour will start in september in texas 
istomin whose wife marta is artistic director of the kennedy 
center for performing arts in washington is always on the move 
last fall he played a recital in brussels ate a sandwich in his 
hotelroom at midnight arose at 5 am to fly to paris where he 
boarded the concorde to new york he was met at kennedy airport 
handed a tuxedo taken to rehearsals for the grammy lifetime 
achievement award show and played that night on the televised show 
to honor isaac stern 
you can not perform to your maximum ability doing it this 
way and i didnt he said its the wrong way to do things 
his intention now is to perform by making short hops from town 
to town for a few years or more 
this tour is the right way to do things he said when you 
play it doesnt have to be only for the fancy swells and 
sophisticates the same kind of people who read the same kind of 
books and listen to the same kind of music live in smaller towns 
the tour began at a college in winter park fla with the 
second concert at a senior citizens center outside miami 
istomin has two programs program a includes bach schubert 
beethoven debussy and chopin he has recorded program b for ada a 
french company that releases compact discs he calls it a bit 
more esoteric schumanns first sonata isnt often played it was 
written to murder the hands of pianists its terribly difficult 
and beautifully inspired not the kind of piece you normally take 
on a barnstorming tour 
he also will play debussy and some infrequently heard 
rachmaninoff on program b thats what my pianos really serve 
for istomin said these pieces require a sophisticated brand 
of piano playing i can offer with these instruments 
istomin has been thinking about a tour such as the one hes 
doing for years i started playing at 17 i played 200 concerts 
in my first two seasons i was soloist with the busch chamber 
orchestra paid 250 a week by columbia artists management 
his first of more than 40 recordings was bachs d minor piano 
concerto with the busch players in 1945 
i played concerts with umbrellas stuck under the sounding 
board and keys that wouldnt go down he said i would 
complain people would say hes a nasty young man the good part 
of it was that some very highlevel musicmaking was done i was 
part of it i know we had a lot of success and people enjoyed the 
concerts 
hell probably give 100 concerts this year too i had the 
stamina half a century ago i hope i have it now the artist 
said im 62 i feel like im 26 and hysterical i think i never 
grew up 
the concerts are strenuous but the traveling is easier these 
days cities are not more than 300 miles apart istomin and the 
piano technician drive by car and luggage oes in the van with the 
piano 
i like playing in unpretentious circumstances he said 
pretention is not the same as excellence i think the public 
wherever the town is people who react to and feel what is 
happening to me thats the whole meaning of this trip 
im not warming up for a program in some big hall ive 
already played these pieces in new york and london i want to play 
in winter park fla the way i play in carnegie hall 
sometimes people ask me to sign a program theyve saved 35 
years those people touch me i want to do something really nice 
for those people for whom music really matters 
istomin played at a general motors cancer research award dinner 
in washington in 1981 
they sent me a check for 7000 my regular fee i sent it 
back donating it to sloan kettering institute for cancer research 
they were touched by that and said to let them know if there was 
ever anything they could do for me when i started thinking about 
this tour i thought maybe they would help me 
gm designed a van with a hydraulic lift and temperature 
control to carry istomins piano and is lending it to him free 
the tour itself doesnt have corporate sponsorship 
