<TEXT>
chain saws have become familiar workhorses around the home as 
homeowners use them to cut firewood and roots clear storm damage 
and trim trees and large shrubbery but many chain saw owners do 
not know how to take care of them properly and can end up with 
costly repair bills 
a chain saw owner needs to perform an annual maintenance check 
to ensure troublefree operation solo inc experts have developed 
a 10step maintenance checklist that can be performed with a few 
standard tools and a little spare time 
you are advised to check the owners manual for specific 
maintenance instructions and to perform the procedures during the 
off season for safety reasons always wear gloves and safety 
glasses when following these steps in maintaining your chain saw 
1 drain any remaining fuel from the saws tank or run the 
engine until it is empty 
2 using a garden hose clean the entire unit while being 
careful not to get water into the gas tank 
3 remove and clean saw chain bar and guide bar dont forget 
to wear gloves 
4 remove spark plug and replace it with a new one every year 
be sure to set the correct spark plug gap 
5 close the choke and remove the air filter assembly clean the 
filter with a stiff paint brush and soap and water or replace it if 
necessary 
6 remove the fuel cap locate the fuel pickline inside the 
tank and fish it out you may want to use an 8inch piece of 
coat hanger that has a u bend at one end replace line or 
filter if dirty and put cap back on the tank 
7 use an allen wrench or screwdriver to remove the starter 
assembly clean filter openings with a rag or brush remove debris 
and replace any worn parts 
8 visually inspect all vibration isolators to be sure they are 
not worn out torn cracked broken or loose check manual for 
exact locations of isolators 
9 check spark plugs arrestor screen for buildup and clean or 
replace if rips or performations are present clean with water or a 
wooden pop stick making sure not to tear holes in the filter 
10 with gloves on grasp muffler to check that it is not loose 
and does not rattle replace if necessary 
when finished double check to make sure all parts have been 
properly replaced all screws and bolts have been tightened and 
there are no pieces left over 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

