the rig count usually declines during the first few months of the 
year 
houstonbased baker hughes an oil toolmaker tallies the number 
of rigs actively exploring for oil and not rigs producing oil the 
rig count is the most widelywatched industry index of drilling 
activity 
hughes tool co which merged this year with baker international 
corp of orange calif has kept track of the number of working 
rigs since 1940 
in december 1981 at the height of the oil boom the count 
reached a peak with 4500 active rigs but in the summer of 1986 
the rig count fell to 663 the lowest since hughes began compiling 
figures as oil prices plunged to less than 10 per 42gallon 
barrel 
