<TEXT>
pan am corp and the union representing 4500 
ground employees in 14 cities remained in a stalemate monday 
following the breakup of their talks and teamster leaders vowed 
guerrilla war against the financially troubled airline 
travel agents reported that some customers have shunned pan am 
flights as a result of the conflict which was sparked after the 
teamsters strike deadline passed at 1201 am sunday 
talks in which management was seeking 35 million in concessions 
from the union broke down sunday afternoon 
no negotiating sessions were held monday the union which 
represents reservation clerks and other ground staff put off a 
strike but teamster leaders threatened to use disruptive tactics 
against pan am which operates pan american world airways a 
northeast corridor air shuttle and other services 
labor unrest also escalated at another major us airline 
flight attendants at minneapolisbased northwest airlines have 
voted overwhelmingly to strike this weekend if a contract dispute 
over wages and benefits is not resolved a union official said 
